node.text:
Visit @SculptMovements 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit! .
Treino de MMI com 01. Agachamento máquina 15/12/10 + drop com extensora 4 x 4 / 4x3 / 4x2 /4x 1 aumentando a carga ( 1 série ) 
1 x 10 com pico de contração em cima + 10 saindo da inércia 
1 x 10 com excêntrica lenta + 10 concêntrica lenta + 10 
02. Stiff 3 x 15 + bom dia 10 
03. Flexora 9 x 6 alternando a carga entre leva e pesado 
1 x 30 curtas + 10 isometria + 12 
1 x unilateral 8 /7/6 até zerar sem intervalo 
04. Flexora em pé 3 x 12 parando no meio + glúteo no cabo 3 x 12 
Panturrilhas sempre 😅
Macacão @santtaloren
.
.
.

node.text:
Tag a friend & visit @EatsConnoisseur for daily delicious foods & recipes to get you slim🥝🍓🍌🍇 

 Butterfly pea flower swirl bread 💙

Ingredients 
240g bread flour *240g 
120g milk of choice 
3 tbsp condensed coconut milk 
2 tbsp sugar of choice 
1 1/2 tsp active dry yeast 
1/4 tsp pink salt

40g dairy free butter 

1 tsp @suncorefoods butterfly pea flower powder *3g (dissolved in 1 tsp water) 

In a stand mixer, add all ingredients except for butter. Mixing on low-medium speed with the hook attachment until the dough comes together, about 10 mins. Add butter, a few pieces at a time. Scrape down the bowl. Continue to kneading on medium speed for 10 mins until the dough is smooth. 

Remove half of the dough from the mixer, set aside. Add butterfly pea flower powder into the half dough and continue kneading until it combined. Knead plain dough and butterfly pea flower dough into balls. Cover let them proof for 1 hour until doubled in size. 

Transfer to a clean surface. Form the dough into a ball and let it rest for 10 mins. Roll out dough until they form thin rectangle. Place butterfly pea flower dough on top of the white dough and begin rolling up the dough along the wide/long side of the rectangle, Place it in a bread pan and let rise until doubled in size, about 1 hour. Bake at 190c for 30 minutes. 

By @nm_meiyee

DUMBBELL FULL BODY 🔥 Visit @SculptMobility for daily pain management, flexibility, and workout advice📚 
.
If you’re training at home or your gym is busy, no worries because I got you 🤩💪🏼 All you need is a pair of dumbbells. Let’s gooooo! ✨
.
ROUTINE:
1️⃣ Squat to front raise 3 x 10-12
2️⃣ Alternating lunge to bicep curl 3 x 12
3️⃣ Single arm clean and press 3 x 8 per side
4️⃣ Plank row 3 x 8 per side
5️⃣ Otis ups 3 x 10
.
.
🎶 Freestyler Will Rock You - Bomfunk MC's vs. Queen vs. P!nk vs. Maroon 5 - SMASH Mashups

credit @mssannamaria

node.text:
💥 New month new goals! 💥 
•
Here’s a few tips for making the best out of your fitness journey:
•
Listen to your body
•
Make sure your rest & recovery are on point, nutrition, sleep, hydration
•
Be ok with making slight adjustments to your program & not having a perfect workout week
•
Make sure that you’re on a program to track progress
•
Do what you can in the time that you have 
•
Strong woman check! Tag a friend who’s up for the challenge! 
Credit @bamfitnesswithbritt

node.text: What they’re saying about @SculptSwim ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ - “The cut is super flattering. Materials are soft and comfortable. This was my first purchase but not my last” Brittany M.

NO EQUIPMENT FULL BODY CIRCUIT✨
.
Who’s ready for a quick and fun sweat sesh, let’s go! 🙋🏼‍♀️
.
CIRCUIT:
Perform exercises 1-5 as an circuit: 30 seconds of work followed by 30 seconds of rest 🔥 Exercises 1 and 3 are 30 seconds per side 👈🏼
Total of 3 rounds with a 3 minute break between the rounds ⚡️
- Exercise 2 can be done knees on the floor for an easier version 🙌🏼

.
🎶 @anthmelo @conormaynard version - Te Bote Remix - Bad Bunny, Ozuna, Nicky Jam

Credit @mssannamaria

Tag a friend & visit @EatsConnoisseur for daily delicious foods & recipes to get you slim🥝🍓🍌🍇

 😋 Yay or Nay? 

By: __daryka__ on TikTok

FULL BODY CIRCUIT ✨ Visit @SculptMobility for daily pain management, flexibility, and workout advice📚 
.
15 reps x 4 rounds of the complete circuit.  This was my routine yesterday!  Normally when I train the upper body I do two muscles (4 exercises and 4 exercises) but I told you that these next few weeks I will be changing a bit of variations and exercises (the body gets used to everything, it is important to always vary). So I just focused on this muscle and did more exercises and it felt awful.  Remember that movements should always be controlled and try to take those short breaks to get the most out of your training!  Come on
 .
 .
 .
 Credit @orianavtorres
